{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπᾰτάω</b> [ᾰπ], <br /> late <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>ἀπατ-έω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Syr.D.” 27 (_passive_)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i> ἠπάτων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 938, _Ionic dialect_ ἐξ-απάτασκον Oracle texts in 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 1070: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> -ήσω: <i>aorist</i> ἠπάτησα, <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἀπ-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.344, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 500 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἠπάτηκα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ph.” 929\">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> ἀπατηθήσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 67a38\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], compare (ἐξ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 436b, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.123\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in <i>middle</i> form ἀπατήσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 262a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], (ἐξ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.3.3\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἠπατήθην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 52e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἠπάτημαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.46, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (ἀπάτη):—<b>cheat, deceive,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.97, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 17.139, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cheat</b> one's <b>hopes,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 462; οἷ᾽ ἠπάτηκας 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 929; κλέμματα.. ἂ τὸν πολέμιον ἀπατήσας 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.9\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be deceptive</b> or <b>fallacious,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1376b28\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be self-deceived, mistaken,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 182, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 594, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 262a, etc.; ἔγνωκα.. φωτὸς ἠπατημένη 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 807\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί γὰρ οὐκ.. ἔρχεται ἀγγελίας ἀπατώμενο; comes not <b>belied by</b> the result? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “El.” 170; ἀ. περί τι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1368b22; περί τινος [prev. author] “Sens.” 442b8; ἀ. ταύτην τὴν ἀπάτην [prev. author] “Anthologia Graeca” 0.74a6\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; also ἀπατᾶσθαι ὡς.. <b>to be deceived into thinking</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 323a.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —The _compound_ ἐξαπατάω is more common, especially in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] and <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose; the simple Verb is used in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Gen.3.13, +others, but not by 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus \">LXX+2nd c.BC+</a>], and is rare in later Greek, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.15d.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0538","accentedUnicode":"ἀπατάω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0539","matchingForm":"ἀπάτη","stepTransliteration":"apatē","gloss":"deceit","_zh_tw_Gloss":"迷惑","_es_Gloss":"engaño","_zh_Gloss":"迷惑"},{"strongNumber":"G1818","matchingForm":"ἐξαπατάω","stepTransliteration":"exapataō","gloss":"to deceive","_zh_tw_Gloss":"誘惑","_es_Gloss":"engañar ","_zh_Gloss":"诱惑"}],"shortDef":"to deceive, cheat, trick","mediumDef":"to deceive, cheat, trick <br /><b>to deceive, seduce into error, cheat, trick</b> <ref='Eph.5.6'>Eph. 5:6;</ref> <ref='1Ti.2.14'>1Tim. 2:14;</ref> <ref='Jas.1.26'>Jas. 1:26</ref>*","stepGloss":"to trick","stepTransliteration":"apataō","count":3,"_es_Definition":"engañar, desviar, corromper","_zh_tw_Definition":"欺騙, 誤導","_zh_Definition":"欺骗, 误导","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"lừa dối; lừa gạt","_zh_tw_Gloss":"被引誘","_es_Gloss":"engañar","_zh_Gloss":"被引诱"}]}